Discreprancy: A lack of consistency; this could apply to the varying degrees of difficulty or complexity encountered when solving a crossword puzzle's clues.

Woodworms: Although not technically white ants, wood-boring insects like termites can also be referred to as "white ants" in certain regions due to their similar appearance and destructive nature on wooden structures.
